				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$C_{{\text{a}}} = \, \left( {{12 }/{\text{ PSII}}t_{{{1}/{2}}} } \right)R,$$\end{document}where R corresponds to the relative energy cost of protein turnover for the reassembly of PSII reaction centers over a diurnal cycle (12 h of daylight).

The available solar radiation across depths, as the energy source for the symbiotic algae to fix inorganic carbon via photosynthesis, is calculated following Kirk13 as:3Ez=E0e-Kdz,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
